{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1100,"text":"Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr.,"},{"time":2750,"text":"in a 1968 speech where he reflects\nupon the Civil Rights Movement,"},{"time":6636,"text":"states, \"In the end,"},{"time":9330,"text":"we will remember not the words of our enemies"},{"time":12413,"text":"but the silence of our friends.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":15280,"text":"As a teacher, I've internalized this message."},{"time":17800,"text":"Every day, all around us,"},{"time":19780,"text":"we see the consequences of silence"},{"time":21456,"text":"manifest themselves in the form of discrimination,"},{"time":23893,"text":"violence, genocide and war."},{"time":27701,"text":"In the classroom, I challenge my students"},{"time":29897,"text":"to explore the silences in their own lives"},{"time":32328,"text":"through poetry."},{"time":34178,"text":"We work together to fill those spaces,"},{"time":36030,"text":"to recognize them, to name them,"},{"time":39308,"text":"to understand that they don't\nhave to be sources of shame."},{"time":42740,"text":"In an effort to create a culture within my classroom"},{"time":45203,"text":"where students feel safe sharing the intimacies"},{"time":47301,"text":"of their own silences,"},{"time":49135,"text":"I have four core principles posted on the board"},{"time":51216,"text":"that sits in the front of my class,"},{"time":53309,"text":"which every student signs\nat the beginning of the year:"},{"time":56370,"text":"read critically, write consciously,"},{"time":58543,"text":"speak clearly, tell your truth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":62408,"text":"And I find myself thinking a lot about that last point,"},{"time":64972,"text":"tell your truth."},{"time":66871,"text":"And I realized that"},{"time":68665,"text":"if I was going to ask my students to speak up,"},{"time":70876,"text":"I was going to have to tell my truth"},{"time":73014,"text":"and be honest with them about the times"},{"time":75280,"text":"where I failed to do so."}]},{"cues":[{"time":76848,"text":"So I tell them that growing up,"},{"time":78908,"text":"as a kid in a Catholic family in New Orleans,"},{"time":81576,"text":"during Lent I was always taught"},{"time":84438,"text":"that the most meaningful thing one could do"},{"time":86246,"text":"was to give something up,"},{"time":87788,"text":"sacrifice something you typically indulge in"},{"time":90080,"text":"to prove to God you understand his sanctity."},{"time":92479,"text":"I've given up soda, McDonald's, French fries,"},{"time":95281,"text":"French kisses, and everything in between."},{"time":98183,"text":"But one year, I gave up speaking."},{"time":102071,"text":"I figured the most valuable thing I could sacrifice"},{"time":104674,"text":"was my own voice, but it was like I hadn't realized"},{"time":108375,"text":"that I had given that up a long time ago."},{"time":111286,"text":"I spent so much of my life"},{"time":113105,"text":"telling people the things they wanted to hear"},{"time":115282,"text":"instead of the things they needed to,"},{"time":116758,"text":"told myself I wasn't meant to be anyone's conscience"},{"time":119174,"text":"because I still had to figure out being my own,"},{"time":121469,"text":"so sometimes I just wouldn't say anything,"},{"time":124701,"text":"appeasing ignorance with my silence,"},{"time":127150,"text":"unaware that validation doesn't need words"},{"time":129547,"text":"to endorse its existence."},{"time":131167,"text":"When Christian was beat up for being gay,"},{"time":132955,"text":"I put my hands in my pocket"},{"time":134223,"text":"and walked with my head\ndown as if I didn't even notice."},{"time":137000,"text":"I couldn't use my locker for weeks\nbecause the bolt on the lock"},{"time":139535,"text":"reminded me of the one I had put on my lips"},{"time":141796,"text":"when the homeless man on the corner"},{"time":143540,"text":"looked at me with eyes up merely searching"},{"time":145320,"text":"for an affirmation that he was worth seeing."},{"time":147502,"text":"I was more concerned with\ntouching the screen on my Apple"},{"time":149607,"text":"than actually feeding him one."},{"time":151170,"text":"When the woman at the fundraising gala"},{"time":152857,"text":"said \"I'm so proud of you."},{"time":154049,"text":"It must be so hard teaching\nthose poor, unintelligent kids,\""},{"time":157120,"text":"I bit my lip, because apparently\nwe needed her money\n"},{"time":159719,"text":"more than my students needed their dignity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161699,"text":"We spend so much time"},{"time":163640,"text":"listening to the things people are saying"},{"time":167540,"text":"that we rarely pay attention to the things they don't."},{"time":170878,"text":"Silence is the residue of fear."},{"time":174139,"text":"It is feeling your flaws"},{"time":175689,"text":"gut-wrench guillotine your tongue."},{"time":177615,"text":"It is the air retreating from your chest"},{"time":179437,"text":"because it doesn't feel safe in your lungs."},{"time":181429,"text":"Silence is Rwandan genocide. Silence is Katrina."},{"time":184553,"text":"It is what you hear when there\naren't enough body bags left."},{"time":187661,"text":"It is the sound after the noose is already tied."},{"time":190062,"text":"It is charring. It is chains. It is privilege. It is pain."},{"time":193409,"text":"There is no time to pick your battles"},{"time":195164,"text":"when your battles have already picked you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196897,"text":"I will not let silence wrap itself around my indecision."},{"time":199960,"text":"I will tell Christian that he is a lion,"},{"time":201927,"text":"a sanctuary of bravery and brilliance."},{"time":204287,"text":"I will ask that homeless man what his name is"},{"time":206683,"text":"and how his day was, because sometimes"},{"time":208393,"text":"all people want to be is human."},{"time":210340,"text":"I will tell that woman that my students can talk about"},{"time":212826,"text":"transcendentalism like their last name was Thoreau,"},{"time":215391,"text":"and just because you watched\none episode of \"The Wire\""},{"time":217426,"text":"doesn't mean you know anything about my kids."},{"time":219665,"text":"So this year,"},{"time":221338,"text":"instead of giving something up,"},{"time":223485,"text":"I will live every day as if there were a microphone"},{"time":225897,"text":"tucked under my tongue,"},{"time":227820,"text":"a stage on the underside of my inhibition."},{"time":231825,"text":"Because who has to have a soapbox"},{"time":233968,"text":"when all you've ever needed is your voice?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":238207,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":240712,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}